-nance-lyceum-theatre-vault-0000013989</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[It's Only a Play]]''\n| Jimmy Wicker\n| [[Bernard B. Jacobs Theatre]], Broadway\n|<ref>http://www.playbill.com/production/its-only-a-play-gerald-schoenfeld-theatre-vault-0000014066</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The Iceman Cometh]]''\n| Theodore \"Hickey\" Hickman\n| [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]]\n|<ref>https://observer.com/2015/02/nathan-lane-raises-a-glass-to-tragedy-in-bams-the-iceman-cometh/</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2016\n| ''[[White Rabbit, Red Rabbit]]''\n| Himself\n| Westside Theatre, Off-Broadway\n|<ref>http://iobdb.com/Production/6174</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Front Page]]''\n| Walter Burns\n| [[Broadhurst Theatre]], Broadway\n| <ref>http://www.playbill.com/production/the-front-page-2016-2017</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| rowspan=2| ''[[Angels in America: A Gay Fantasia on National Themes|Angels in America]]''\n| rowspan=2| [[Roy Cohn]]\n| [[Lyttelton Theatre]], London\n|<ref>https://www.nationaltheatre.org.uk/shows/angels-in-america</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| [[Neil Simon Theatre]], Broadway\n| <ref>http://www.playbill.com/production/angels-in-america-perestroika-neil-simon-theatre-2017-2018</ref> \n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Gary: A Sequel to Titus Andronicus]]''\n| Gary\n| [[Booth Theatre]], Broadway\n|<ref>http://www.playbill.com/production/gary-a-sequel-to-titus-andronicus-booth-theatre-2018-2019</ref>\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[Disney's Animated Storybook|Animated Storybook: The Lion King]]''\n| Timon\n| Voice\n|}\n\n===Other===\n* Presented [[Mike Birbiglia]]'s (2008) [[Off-Broadway]] show ''Sleepwalk With Me''.\n* Lane provided the voice of [[Innoventions (Disneyland)|Tom Morrow]], the [[Audio-Animatronic]] host of [[Disneyland]]'s [[Innoventions (Disneyland)|Innoventions]] attraction.\n* Children's book ''Naughty Mabel'', written with husband Devlin Elliott, published by Simon and Schuster, released in October 2015. A second book, ''Naughty Mabel Sees It All'' was released in October 2016.\n* Wrote the introduction to ''Neil Simon's Memoirs'', published by Simon and Schuster.\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n=== Film accolades ===\n'''Golden Globe Award'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Accolades\n!Results\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[The Birdcage]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Musical or Comedy|Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Musical or Comedy]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2006\n|''[[The Producers (2005 film)|The Producers]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Musical or Comedy|Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Musical or Comedy]]\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n'''Screen Actors Guild Award'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Accolade\n!Results\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[The Birdcage]]''\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Motion Picture]]\n|{{WON}}\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[The Birdcage]]''\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Supporting Role|Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Supporting Role]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|}\n\n'''Miscellaneous Awards'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Accolade\n!Results\n|-\n|1996\n|''[[Jeffrey (1995 film)|Jeffrey]]''\n|[[American Comedy Awards|American Comedy Award, Funniest Supporting Actor in a Motion Picture]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[The Birdcage]]''\n|[[American Comedy Awards|American Comedy Award, Funniest Lead Actor in a Motion Picture]]\n|{{WON}}\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[The Birdcage]]''\n|[[Chicago Film Critics Association Award for Best Supporting Actor|Chicago Film Critics Association Award, Best Supporting Actor]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[The Birdcage]]''\n|[[MTV Movie Award for Best On-Screen Duo|MTV Movie + TV Award, Best On-Screen Duo]] (<small>shared with [[Robin Williams]]</small>)\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[The Birdcage]]''\n|Onlin